<div id="review_123543538" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/123543538" />
    <a title="Jeff" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/195212-jeff"><img alt="Jeff" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1184617117p2/195212.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/123543538?book_show_action=true">Sep 26, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeff" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeff" href="/user/show/195212-jeff">Jeff</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer123543538" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12847169016654138876">This is a great collection of short stories by Fritz Leiber, who was a true master of science fiction, fantasy and horror, as well as a long autobiographical essay by Mr. Leiber.<br/><br/>As the title would indicate, several of the stories are ghost stories (in fact, the title story is one of the best and most bizarre ghost stories I have ever read), some venture into magical realism, there is a Fafhrd and Gray Mouser tale, plus &quot;Space Time for Springers&quot; (which every cat lover should read).<br/><br/>The autobiogap</span>
  <span id="freeText12847169016654138876" style="display:none">This is a great collection of short stories by Fritz Leiber, who was a true master of science fiction, fantasy and horror, as well as a long autobiographical essay by Mr. Leiber.<br /><br />As the title would indicate, several of the stories are ghost stories (in fact, the title story is one of the best and most bizarre ghost stories I have ever read), some venture into magical realism, there is a Fafhrd and Gray Mouser tale, plus "Space Time for Springers" (which every cat lover should read).<br /><br />The autobiogaphical essay was interesting but left me wanting more. I wish it had been longer and had gone into more detail but, as Mr. Leiber pointed out, he preferred writing fiction to writing about himself.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12847169016654138876" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
